						<p>In NLP, tasks are usually realized using two main analysis methods: syntactic analysis and semantic analysis. The syntactic analysis assesses a text’s meaningfulness and attempts to align it with grammatical rules. On the other hand, semantics analysis tries to capture the meaning that is conveyed by the text that syntactic analysis overlooks.</p>
					<p>As you can probably see, semantic analysis is a bit more difficult than syntactic analysis. That being said, semantic analysis remains one of those unresolved NLP problems.</p>


